Primary key is used to identify each records of a table uniquely.
Primary key column must be unique. It always contains a unique value.
Primary key column doen't accept duplicate values.
Primary key column cann't be null or empty.
Primary key must be assigned compulsory for the columns defined with auto_increment constraint.
A table can have or can't have a primary key. It is not compulsory.
A table can have only 1 primary key. Multiple keys are not accepted.
In a table there may be one primay key or many other fileds also have primary key by combining together.
We can add primary key in a table by 2 ways- while creating table and also by alter the existing table later.
We can able to drop/delete primary key after table creation,except the above point no.5
